<HEAD>ODE for the proce&s;&s;ion, at the end of the fifth act.</HEAD>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>CHORUS of PRIESTS and BARDS.</SPEAKER>
<L>HE's fled, he's gone! th' immortal bard,</L>
<L>Who&s;e &s;ong would charm a &s;avage pard,</L>
<L>Fled to return no more!</L>
<L><HI>Parna&s;&s;us</HI> drops its towering head,</L>
<L><HI>Apollo</HI> wails the fav'rite dead;</L>
<L>His lo&s;s the NINE deplore.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>CHORUS of PRIESTS and VIRGINS.</SPEAKER>
<L>She's fled! the lovely nymph is gone!</L>
<L>Who&s;e charms would fire a brea&s;t of &s;tone;</L>
<L>Fled never to return!</L>
<L><HI>Diana</HI> and the <HI>Cyprian</HI> queen,</L>
<L>With cea&s;ele&s;s &s;ighs, and tri&s;tful mien,</L>
<L>Their breathle&s;s fav'rite mourn.</L>
</SP>
<STAGE>RECITATIVE.</STAGE>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Bards.</SPEAKER>
<L>Of temper &s;weet, of manners mild &mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Virgins.</SPEAKER>
<L>She was a dear, an only child &mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Bards.</SPEAKER>
<L>Such harmony his numbers ble&s;s'd &mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Virgins.</SPEAKER>
<L>Such dignity her per&s;on grac'd &mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Bards.</SPEAKER>
<L>Such maje&s;ty his lays attended &mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Virgins.</SPEAKER>
<L>Such &s;ov'reignty her mein befriended &mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Bards.</SPEAKER>
<L>He was the tuneful &s;i&s;ters' boa&s;t &mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Virgins.</SPEAKER>
<L>And of <HI>St. Giles</HI>'s &s;he the toa&s;t: &mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Bards.</SPEAKER>
<L>'Mong&s;t wits he claim'd the highe&s;t po&s;t, &mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Virgins.</SPEAKER>
<L>'Mong&s;t faire&s;t nymphs &s;he rul'd the roa&s;t. &mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>CHORUS of PRIESTS, BARDS, and VIRGINS.</SPEAKER>
<L>He was the tuneful &s;i&s;ters' boa&s;t,</L>
<L>And of <HI>St. Giles</HI>'s &s;he the toa&s;t;</L>
